{
  "texts": [
    "The work of Lyu and Shu (2021) requires further optimization to reduce the memory and time constraint limitations.",
    "Additionally, future work includes experimenting with combining two attention mechanisms.",
    "So far we have analyzed static 3D shapes; however, for VAEs dynamic models also exist.",
    "Starting from the comprehensive survey on human pose estimation created by Wang et al. (2021a), or on face alignments by Gogić et al. (2021), we conclude that human poses, being very complex entities, offer a practical base for dynamic modeling.",
    "Approximating motion from a pose is a possibility, as described by Yan et al. (2018), where they created a human motion generator using VAE, called Motion Transformation Variational Auto-Encoders (MTVAE)."
  ]
}